related_post.text: does anybody know why gofmt decides to nest this fn 2 levels? ```gofunc BenchmarkLoop(thing string) (func() func()) { now := time.Now() last := now duras := []time.Duration{} return func() { looped := time.Now() duras = append(duras looped.Sub(last)) last = looped }, func() { Debugln(thing took cumulatively time.Now().Sub(now) individually: duras) }}```
